  "title": "when binding events to document, in some cases, event.target is not bound to the DOM",
  "body": "**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\nwhen clicking a checkbox inside the `refinementList` widget, the triggered event sometimes has a event.target not being bind to the DOM.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce 🔍**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\nLet's say you have `document.addEventListener('click', myFunction)` (with `myFunction` being defined).\r\nYou create an instantsearch with a `refinementList` widget.\r\nYou clic multiple time on that widget's first checkbox.\r\nEach time you do so, `myFunction` is called with an `event` object.\r\nAfter the first time it is called, the `event.target` that `myFunction` receives is not bind to the DOM\r\n\r\nLive example:\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/ais-ecommerce-demo-app-g06se\r\n_Look at the Console logs_\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior 💭**\r\nThe `event.target` should always be binded to the DOM.\r\n\r\n**Environment:**\r\n - Browser at least chrome\r\n - Version at least latest (78 at time of writing)\r\n",
